# SnippetForge — environment variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to `.env` for LOCAL development ONLY. Never commit `.env`.
# In production, set these in your host's dashboard:
#   Vercel:  Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   Netlify: Site configuration → Environment variables
# The variable NAME must be exactly OPENAI_API_KEY (all caps, underscore).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REQUIRED — your OpenAI secret key. Powers the ✨ "Generate with AI" features.
# Get one at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys  (requires billing/credit on OpenAI)
# This value stays SERVER-SIDE only (read by api/generate.js on Vercel and
# netlify/functions/generate.js on Netlify). It is never shipped to the browser
# or baked into index.html.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-secret-key-here

# OPTIONAL — override the model used for AI copy generation.
# Defaults to gpt-4o-mini (fast + cheap) if unset.
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# OPTIONAL — restrict which origin may call /api/generate.
# Defaults to "*" (same-origin fetches work fine either way).
# ALLOWED_ORIGIN=https://yoursite.com

# NOTE — PayPal:
# There is NO PayPal secret here. The PayPal *Client ID* is a public value that
# lives in index.html (const PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID). Swap in your LIVE Client ID from
# developer.paypal.com to receive real payments. See README.md.
